# trafficdesign UI Kit - Cursor Rules

When building UI components in this project, follow these guidelines:

## Required Files

Include these files in your HTML:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="dist/td-ui-kit.css">
<script src="dist/td-ui-kit.js"></script>
```

For charts, also include:
```html
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/apexcharts"></script>
<script src="dist/td-charts.js"></script>
```

## Documentation

- **Quick Reference**: See `docs/AI-CONTEXT.md` for a compact class overview
- **Full Documentation**: See `docs/COMPONENTS.md` for complete examples
- **Theming**: See `docs/THEMING.md` for customization

## Key CSS Classes

### Buttons
- `.btn .btn-primary` - Primary action
- `.btn .btn-secondary` - Secondary action
- `.btn .btn-ghost` - Tertiary/ghost
- `.btn .btn-danger` - Destructive action
- `.btn .btn-success` - Positive action
- Sizes: `.btn-xs`, `.btn-sm`, `.btn-lg`

### Cards
- `.card-tool` - Main card container
- `.card-tool-header` - Card header with border
- `.card-tool-body` - Card content area
- `.card-tool-footer` - Card footer with gray background

### Forms
- `.input-field` - Text inputs
- `.select-field` - Select dropdowns
- `.toggle` + `.toggle-handle` - Toggle switches
- `.label` - Form labels (add `.label-required` for required)
- Validation: `.input-field-error`, `.input-field-success`

### Tables
- `.table-tool` - Base table
- `.table-tool-striped` - Zebra striping
- `.table-tool-compact` - Compact spacing

### Alerts & Badges
- `.alert .alert-success|warning|error|info`
- `.badge .badge-primary|success|warning|error|info|neutral`

### Navigation
- `.sidebar` with `.sidebar-link` and `.sidebar-link-active`
- `.topbar` for header
- `.breadcrumbs` for breadcrumb navigation
- `.tabs` with `.tab` and `.tab-active`

## JavaScript API

```javascript
// Show notifications
notify('Message', 'success'); // success|error|warning|info

// Modal control
TDUI.openModal('modal-id');
TDUI.closeModal('modal-id');

// Sidebar
TDUI.toggleSidebar();

// Utilities
TDUI.formatNumber(12345);     // "12.345"
TDUI.formatCurrency(99.99);   // "99,99 â‚¬"
```

## Data Attributes

- `data-dropdown-trigger` - Opens parent dropdown
- `data-modal-open="id"` - Opens modal with given ID
- `data-modal-close` - Closes parent modal
- `data-tab="id"` - Switches to tab panel
- `data-tooltip="text"` - Shows tooltip on hover

## Design Principles

1. Use semantic HTML (`<button>` for actions, `<a>` for links)
2. Add `aria-label` for icon-only buttons
3. Use the predefined utility classes for spacing/layout
4. Follow the existing patterns in `examples/` directory
5. Use CSS variables for theming (see `docs/THEMING.md`)

## Color Palette

- Primary: `--td-brand-primary` (#00AFCE)
- Success: `--td-success` (#22C55E)
- Warning: `--td-warning` (#F59E0B)
- Error: `--td-error` (#EF4444)
- Info: `--td-info` (#3B82F6)
- Grays: `--td-surface-50` to `--td-surface-900`

